You may would like to install Tensorflow(CPU) on your own PC, just do following things will be okay:

1.Anaconda3-4.4.0(Once you install Anaconda, you don't have to install Python)
After installed Anaconda3,you should have a try if it is be done:
Type 'python' in cmd, and then type 'import numpy','import matplotlib' respectively.
If not work, please remember to add to 'path'.

2.Tensorflow
Add 'pip' to 'path' firstly.
And after that type 'python -m pip install--upgrade --ignore-installed tensorflow' in cmd.
After all of this, just have a try by typing 'import tensorflow' in 'python' of cmd.
